               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270913-183-person1747">
                  CHARLES 
                  NEWTON
               <interp inst="t18270913-183-person1747" type="surname" value="NEWTON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-183-person1747" type="given" value="CHARLES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-183-person1747" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am servant to Mr. Thomas Green Phillips, a <rs id="t18270913-183-viclabel1038" type="occupation">hatter</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270913-183-victim1746 t18270913-183-viclabel1038"></join>, of Hackney-road. On the 2d of August, about two o'clock in the day. I saw the prisoner about two hundred yards from Mr. Phillips', with this hat on his head. I went up to him - he stopped, took it off, and said"Is this your hat?" I took it from him, and he ran away. I followed, and cried Stop thief! - he was taken in Union-street.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. PHILLIPS. Q. Where did you place it? A. On a rail outside of the door, tied with a string. I did not see him untie it.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270913-183-person1748">
                  RICHARD 
                  RILEY
               <interp inst="t18270913-183-person1748" type="surname" value="RILEY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-183-person1748" type="given" value="RICHARD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-183-person1748" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an officer. I took the prisoner, and produce the hat.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270913-183-person1749">
                  THOMAS 
                  GREEN PHILLIPS
               <interp inst="t18270913-183-person1749" type="surname" value="GREEN PHILLIPS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-183-person1749" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-183-person1749" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a hatter. This hat is mine - it was outside my door. I know nothing of the prisoner.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined. Q. How many hats do you tie outside your door? A. Sometimes twelve - it is a great thoroughfare, but it is a wide pavement. Four witnesses gave the prisoner a good character, one of whom engaged to take him into his employ.</p>
               <p>GUILTY. Aged 16.</p>
